The paper deals with distributed algorithms for autonomous mobile robots, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems), which focuses on the study of systems composed of multiple interacting agents, such as robots. The second likely category is cs.RO (Robotics), which deals with the design, construction, and operation of robots. The third likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), which deals with the design and analysis of algorithms for distributed systems. The fourth likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), which deals with the analysis and control of complex systems, such as autonomous robots. The fifth likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which deals with the development of algorithms that enable machines to learn from data and make decisions.
